@startuml multilingual-flow
' Detect → route → rescore activity flow for the multilingual correction pipeline.
' LanguageDetector picks argmax_ℓ P(ℓ | context) per span; CodeSwitchTransducer
' resolves switch points; each span is rescored by its per-language LanguageModel.
' Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md (Correction & NLP = amber #FFF59D / #F9A825;
' Foundation = blue #BBDEFB / #1565C0; Neutral/IO = #ECEFF1 / #455A64).
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #FFF59D
  BorderColor #F9A825
  FontColor #102027
  DiamondBackgroundColor #BBDEFB
  DiamondBorderColor #1565C0
  StartColor #1565C0
  EndColor #2E7D32
}

title <b>Multilingual correction</b>  —  detect → route → rescore

start
:Tokenize input into words;
note right #ECEFF1
  words: ["hello", "mundo"]
end note

:<b>LanguageDetector.detect_word</b>\nargmax<sub>ℓ</sub> P(ℓ | context)\nper word / span;
#BBDEFB:Code-switch present?\n(more than one ℓ argmax);
if (yes) then (switch)
  :<b>CodeSwitchTransducer.best_path</b>\nViterbi over (word × language)\nwith switch_penalty;
  :Segment into LanguageSpans\n(contiguous single-language runs);
else (monolingual)
  :Single LanguageSpan\n= whole utterance;
endif

:Route each span to its\nper-language <b>LanguageModel</b>;
fork
  :Rescore en span\nLanguageModel("en");
fork again
  :Rescore es span\nLanguageModel("es");
end fork

:Recombine spans into one\nscored hypothesis;
#C8E6C9:Emit CodeSwitchPath\n(word_languages, switch_points, score);
stop
@enduml
